  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A 55-year-old man comes to the physician because of a 2-month history of headaches, facial numbness, recurrent epistaxis, and a 5-kg (11-lb) weight loss. He recently immigrated from Hong Kong. Examination shows right-sided cervical lymphadenopathy. Endoscopy shows an exophytic nasopharyngeal mass. Histologic examination of a biopsy specimen of the mass shows sheets of undifferentiated cells with nuclear pleomorphism and abundant mitotic figures. The patient most likely acquired the causal pathogen of his nasopharyngeal mass via which of the following routes of transmission?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Sexual contact"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Tick bite"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Transfer of saliva"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Fecal-oral"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Blood transfusion"
        },
        {
          "id": 6,
          "text": "Mother to baby"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>Disease transmitted via sexual contact include <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mf0V52&anker=Z318c3fdbcf10c252f3453a2394e29d91\" data-learningcard-id=\"mf0V52\" data-anker=\"Z318c3fdbcf10c252f3453a2394e29d91\" data-section-id=\"8S0OYf\" data-sememe-id=\"Dj01cT\">human immunodeficiency virus</a></span>, <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zO0rET&anker=Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-learningcard-id=\"zO0rET\" data-anker=\"Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-section-id=\"CPbqSF\" data-sememe-id=\"4kY3L6\">human papillomavirus</a></span>, and <span data-sememe-id=\"yE1dyi0\">herpes simplex virus</span>. In rare cases, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mf0M52&anker=Z3dc5e5e8167ee0fcff3292d08c7a19b2\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mf0M52\" data-anker=\"Z3dc5e5e8167ee0fcff3292d08c7a19b2\" data-section-id=\"PpXWp_\" data-sememe-id=\"CnaqvO\">EBV</a> may be transmitted through genital secretions (suggests the possibility of sexual transmission); however, this possibility is less likely when compared to more common routes of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mf0M52&anker=Z3dc5e5e8167ee0fcff3292d08c7a19b2\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mf0M52\" data-anker=\"Z3dc5e5e8167ee0fcff3292d08c7a19b2\" data-section-id=\"PpXWp_\" data-sememe-id=\"CnaqvO\">EBV</a> transmission.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>Although ticks are a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Qn0uGg&anker=Z49eaab315eec740b0956668ef8276593\" data-learningcard-id=\"Qn0uGg\" data-anker=\"Z49eaab315eec740b0956668ef8276593\" data-section-id=\"0aceQa0\" data-sememe-id=\"hi0crf\">vector</a> for a number of diseases such as <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4f03m2&anker=Z7529403f563fdcd40cad6e73a3473868\" data-learningcard-id=\"4f03m2\" data-anker=\"Z7529403f563fdcd40cad6e73a3473868\" data-sememe-id=\"Fj0gXT\">Lyme disease</a></span> (<i><span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4f03m2&anker=Z04126a47ac3ffb55c31045fd1523f70b\" data-learningcard-id=\"4f03m2\" data-anker=\"Z04126a47ac3ffb55c31045fd1523f70b\" data-section-id=\"hg0cE2\" data-sememe-id=\"_cX5UC\">Ixodes scapularis</a></span></i> tick), <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=P70WNh&anker=Z3499e2e7a0463f85dd2bcbb979f04fa9\" data-learningcard-id=\"P70WNh\" data-anker=\"Z3499e2e7a0463f85dd2bcbb979f04fa9\" data-section-id=\"Tt161i0\" data-sememe-id=\"zabrMH\">babesiosis</a></span> (<i><span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4f03m2&anker=Z04126a47ac3ffb55c31045fd1523f70b\" data-learningcard-id=\"4f03m2\" data-anker=\"Z04126a47ac3ffb55c31045fd1523f70b\" data-section-id=\"hg0cE2\" data-sememe-id=\"_cX5UC\">Ixodes scapularis</a></span></i> tick), and <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=P70WNh&anker=Zbb8143ef176ead7b35eebdf1cf5240fe\" data-learningcard-id=\"P70WNh\" data-anker=\"Zbb8143ef176ead7b35eebdf1cf5240fe\" data-section-id=\"gt1F1i0\" data-sememe-id=\"_ab5MH\">ehrlichiosis</a></span> (<span class=\"linksuggest\"><span data-sememe-id=\"zcXrUC\">lone star tick</span></span>), they play no role in the transmission of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mf0M52&anker=Z3dc5e5e8167ee0fcff3292d08c7a19b2\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mf0M52\" data-anker=\"Z3dc5e5e8167ee0fcff3292d08c7a19b2\" data-section-id=\"PpXWp_\" data-sememe-id=\"CnaqvO\">EBV</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) CORRECT:</h4>\n<span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mf0M52&anker=Z3dc5e5e8167ee0fcff3292d08c7a19b2\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mf0M52\" data-anker=\"Z3dc5e5e8167ee0fcff3292d08c7a19b2\" data-section-id=\"PpXWp_\" data-sememe-id=\"CnaqvO\">EBV</a> </b></span>is mainly transmitted through <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>saliva </b></span>and <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>respiratory secretions</b></span>. In addition to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Cj0qcT&anker=Z3fcbbe8cb77e7c63a6bfdffb314cb871\" data-learningcard-id=\"Cj0qcT\" data-anker=\"Z3fcbbe8cb77e7c63a6bfdffb314cb871\" data-section-id=\"mOYVG6\" data-sememe-id=\"LjXway\">nasopharyngeal carcinoma</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mf0M52&anker=Z3dc5e5e8167ee0fcff3292d08c7a19b2\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mf0M52\" data-anker=\"Z3dc5e5e8167ee0fcff3292d08c7a19b2\" data-section-id=\"PpXWp_\" data-sememe-id=\"CnaqvO\">EBV</a> is associated with the development of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Lf0w52&anker=Z396e86e88d3315f2dd9b99cf38d0942c\" data-learningcard-id=\"Lf0w52\" data-anker=\"Z396e86e88d3315f2dd9b99cf38d0942c\" data-sememe-id=\"Cj0qcT\">infectious mononucleosis</a> (“<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Lf0w52&anker=Z396e86e88d3315f2dd9b99cf38d0942c\" data-learningcard-id=\"Lf0w52\" data-anker=\"Z396e86e88d3315f2dd9b99cf38d0942c\" data-sememe-id=\"Cj0qcT\">kissing disease</a>”), <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=9j0NcT&anker=Z92e7c173e5da863cff38964da0ce27f6\" data-learningcard-id=\"9j0NcT\" data-anker=\"Z92e7c173e5da863cff38964da0ce27f6\" data-section-id=\"5tXiV-\" data-sememe-id=\"sYbtqH\">oral hairy leukoplakia</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=1o02aS&anker=Zd938fcdc5e48d00d7a21c4dcb095c19a\" data-learningcard-id=\"1o02aS\" data-anker=\"Zd938fcdc5e48d00d7a21c4dcb095c19a\" data-section-id=\"_Qc5AX0\" data-sememe-id=\"lTbvIG\">primary CNS lymphoma</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mT0Vr2&anker=Z419133b57ea628b183f73a28c5ad7a8c\" data-learningcard-id=\"mT0Vr2\" data-anker=\"Z419133b57ea628b183f73a28c5ad7a8c\" data-sememe-id=\"5P0i2T\">Hodgkin lymphoma</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=NT0-I2&anker=Z32e75670957f333d32b69d362f460757\" data-learningcard-id=\"NT0-I2\" data-anker=\"Z32e75670957f333d32b69d362f460757\" data-section-id=\"F4cgOc0\" data-sememe-id=\"7I04Vh\">Burkitt lymphoma</a>. Most individuals have a latent <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Lf0w52&anker=Z396e86e88d3315f2dd9b99cf38d0942c\" data-learningcard-id=\"Lf0w52\" data-anker=\"Z396e86e88d3315f2dd9b99cf38d0942c\" data-sememe-id=\"Cj0qcT\">EBV infection</a>, but malignant complications typically occur only after reactivation in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=x50Emg&anker=Z1af19ecc772907dd339670b5fb0e8b51\" data-learningcard-id=\"x50Emg\" data-anker=\"Z1af19ecc772907dd339670b5fb0e8b51\" data-section-id=\"h_XcL00\" data-sememe-id=\"P2YW3o\">immunocompromised individuals</a> (e.g., patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mf0V52&anker=Z318c3fdbcf10c252f3453a2394e29d91\" data-learningcard-id=\"mf0V52\" data-anker=\"Z318c3fdbcf10c252f3453a2394e29d91\" data-section-id=\"8S0OYf\" data-sememe-id=\"Dj01cT\">HIV</a>).</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>The fecal-oral route is the primary route of transmission of many pathogens, such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ff0gL2&anker=Ze09d3cf63ef1a16aa7f42af8f475cdb4\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ff0gL2\" data-anker=\"Ze09d3cf63ef1a16aa7f42af8f475cdb4\" data-sememe-id=\"aP0QWT\">helminths</a> (e.g., <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ff0gL2&anker=Z3bdf0551665f902bb7f7437f1345d942\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ff0gL2\" data-anker=\"Z3bdf0551665f902bb7f7437f1345d942\" data-section-id=\"MpXMJ_\" data-sememe-id=\"jLa_xO\">ascariasis</a></span>, <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ff0gL2&anker=Z626348337721606624cdbdbddc89d761\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ff0gL2\" data-anker=\"Z626348337721606624cdbdbddc89d761\" data-section-id=\"5pXiJ_\" data-sememe-id=\"QLauxO\">enterobiasis</a>),</span> <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=kS0m-2&anker=Z1ed76748d77360ed31c0ffae5f7a8a3f\" data-learningcard-id=\"kS0m-2\" data-anker=\"Z1ed76748d77360ed31c0ffae5f7a8a3f\" data-sememe-id=\"w40hlT\">hepatitis A</a></span>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pn0Wtg&anker=Z0f5ee027e23cb007828cee029e1f332b\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pn0Wtg\" data-anker=\"Z0f5ee027e23cb007828cee029e1f332b\" data-section-id=\"fackPa0\" data-sememe-id=\"ZlYZv6\">hepatitis E</a>. <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mf0M52&anker=Z3dc5e5e8167ee0fcff3292d08c7a19b2\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mf0M52\" data-anker=\"Z3dc5e5e8167ee0fcff3292d08c7a19b2\" data-section-id=\"PpXWp_\" data-sememe-id=\"CnaqvO\">EBV</a></span> is not transmitted <span data-sememe-id=\"HCcKte0\">fecal-orally</span>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=2M0TLg&anker=Z0d767a500a4efcb1314a93ab2616de44\" data-learningcard-id=\"2M0TLg\" data-anker=\"Z0d767a500a4efcb1314a93ab2616de44\" data-sememe-id=\"jo0_bS\">Blood transfusions</a></span> carry the risk of transmitting some <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pn0Wtg&anker=Zcdc83877f75d9d9b9a07ece6544f646c\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pn0Wtg\" data-anker=\"Zcdc83877f75d9d9b9a07ece6544f646c\" data-section-id=\"VacGja0\">viruses</a>, such as <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=OS0I-2&anker=Z8400c8767de06bd1fa7338aa79959829\" data-learningcard-id=\"OS0I-2\" data-anker=\"Z8400c8767de06bd1fa7338aa79959829\" data-sememe-id=\"940NlT\">hepatitis B</a></span>, <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=lS0v-2&anker=Z5917fb5ac1ad1902eb48a7e3fc736c08\" data-learningcard-id=\"lS0v-2\" data-anker=\"Z5917fb5ac1ad1902eb48a7e3fc736c08\" data-sememe-id=\"C40qlT\">hepatitis C</a></span>, and <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mf0V52&anker=Z318c3fdbcf10c252f3453a2394e29d91\" data-learningcard-id=\"mf0V52\" data-anker=\"Z318c3fdbcf10c252f3453a2394e29d91\" data-section-id=\"8S0OYf\" data-sememe-id=\"Dj01cT\">human immunodeficiency virus</a></span> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mf0V52&anker=Z318c3fdbcf10c252f3453a2394e29d91\" data-learningcard-id=\"mf0V52\" data-anker=\"Z318c3fdbcf10c252f3453a2394e29d91\" data-section-id=\"8S0OYf\" data-sememe-id=\"Dj01cT\">HIV</a>). Although there is a risk of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=2M0TLg&anker=Z0d767a500a4efcb1314a93ab2616de44\" data-learningcard-id=\"2M0TLg\" data-anker=\"Z0d767a500a4efcb1314a93ab2616de44\" data-sememe-id=\"jo0_bS\">transfusion</a>-related <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mf0M52&anker=Z3dc5e5e8167ee0fcff3292d08c7a19b2\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mf0M52\" data-anker=\"Z3dc5e5e8167ee0fcff3292d08c7a19b2\" data-section-id=\"PpXWp_\" data-sememe-id=\"CnaqvO\">EBV</a></span> infection among some patients (e.g., <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=uo0pdS&anker=Z84c49626f7daebca811b981e8045a644\" data-learningcard-id=\"uo0pdS\" data-anker=\"Z84c49626f7daebca811b981e8045a644\" data-section-id=\"zKcrQW0\">stem cell</a> transplant recipients), this risk is considerably low when compared to other more common routes of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mf0M52&anker=Z3dc5e5e8167ee0fcff3292d08c7a19b2\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mf0M52\" data-anker=\"Z3dc5e5e8167ee0fcff3292d08c7a19b2\" data-section-id=\"PpXWp_\" data-sememe-id=\"CnaqvO\">EBV</a> transmission.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>F) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=d40oRT&anker=Z8916e5f23e9fb026689a4803249d708d\" data-learningcard-id=\"d40oRT\" data-anker=\"Z8916e5f23e9fb026689a4803249d708d\" data-section-id=\"OuXIr-\" data-sememe-id=\"oZX0c9\">Vertical transmission</a></span> (i.e., from mother to baby) can occur with many pathogens, such as <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mf0V52&anker=Z318c3fdbcf10c252f3453a2394e29d91\" data-learningcard-id=\"mf0V52\" data-anker=\"Z318c3fdbcf10c252f3453a2394e29d91\" data-section-id=\"8S0OYf\" data-sememe-id=\"Dj01cT\">human immunodeficiency virus</a></span>, <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=OS0I-2&anker=Z8400c8767de06bd1fa7338aa79959829\" data-learningcard-id=\"OS0I-2\" data-anker=\"Z8400c8767de06bd1fa7338aa79959829\" data-sememe-id=\"940NlT\">hepatitis B</a></span> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pn0Wtg&anker=Zcdc83877f75d9d9b9a07ece6544f646c\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pn0Wtg\" data-anker=\"Zcdc83877f75d9d9b9a07ece6544f646c\" data-section-id=\"VacGja0\">virus</a>, <span class=\"linksuggest\">Group B <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Sn0ysg&anker=Zc55380d620c82ec8d6a1edfc63b9bfbf\" data-learningcard-id=\"Sn0ysg\" data-anker=\"Zc55380d620c82ec8d6a1edfc63b9bfbf\" data-section-id=\"r0cfha0\" data-sememe-id=\"FQYgBK\">streptococcus</a></span>, and <i><span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Sn0ysg&anker=Z64d03038beee5f68c994277cf1b40437\" data-learningcard-id=\"Sn0ysg\" data-anker=\"Z64d03038beee5f68c994277cf1b40437\" data-section-id=\"H0cKha0\" data-sememe-id=\"ejYxzK\">Listeria monocytogenes</a></span></i>. Although some studies suggest the possibility of <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mf0M52&anker=Z3dc5e5e8167ee0fcff3292d08c7a19b2\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mf0M52\" data-anker=\"Z3dc5e5e8167ee0fcff3292d08c7a19b2\" data-section-id=\"PpXWp_\" data-sememe-id=\"CnaqvO\">EBV</a></span> transmission in utero or during delivery, other modes of transmission are more likely.</div>",
      "hint": "Headaches, facial numbness (due to cranial nerve involvement), recurrent epistaxis, weight loss, and lymphadenopathy are suggestive of malignancy. The biopsy of this patient's mass shows undifferentiated nasopharyngeal carcinoma, which commonly occurs in adults of Southeast Asian descent. Epstein-Barr virus (EBV) is the primary causative agent in the pathogenesis of this condition.",
