      "text": "A 65-year-old man presents with a 6-week history of halitosis, mild sore throat, and pain in his right ear. He is otherwise healthy, has a 50-pack-year history of cigarette smoking, and drinks alcohol almost every day.\nExamination of the oral cavity and oropharynx reveals that the right tonsil is erythematous, with a 1-cm area of ulceration that has irregular borders. One of the upper cervical lymph nodes on the right is enlarged (3 cm). No trismus is evident.\nWhich one of the following diagnoses is most likely for this patient?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Squamous-cell carcinoma"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Group A streptococcal pharyngitis"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Infectious mononucleosis"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Non-Hodgkin lymphoma"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Tonsilloliths secondary to cryptic tonsils"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) CORRECT:</h4>A unilateral ulcerative tonsillar lesion in the setting of neck <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=iL0Jxg&anker=Z9a24d08ab67dee43098222189f24cc1a\" data-learningcard-id=\"iL0Jxg\" data-anker=\"Z9a24d08ab67dee43098222189f24cc1a\" data-sememe-id=\"OCYIHr\">lymphadenopathy</a> is cancer until proven otherwise. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z17c54b50884f6ae691e10c71ea7eccb6\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z17c54b50884f6ae691e10c71ea7eccb6\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\" data-sememe-id=\"prXLRz\">Squamous-cell carcinoma</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z17c54b50884f6ae691e10c71ea7eccb6\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z17c54b50884f6ae691e10c71ea7eccb6\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\" data-sememe-id=\"prXLRz\">SCC</a>) accounts for 90% of cancers in the head and neck, with the most common <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ps0LDh&anker=Zbc0d0ff153bc5c7a27589815d0c842fd\" data-learningcard-id=\"ps0LDh\" data-anker=\"Zbc0d0ff153bc5c7a27589815d0c842fd\" data-section-id=\"FfWgLk0\" data-sememe-id=\"b31HSg0\">risk factors</a> being tobacco and <span data-sememe-id=\"NoW-Xm0\">alcohol</span> use. Recent evidence suggests that infection with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zO0rET&anker=Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-learningcard-id=\"zO0rET\" data-anker=\"Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-section-id=\"CPbqSF\" data-sememe-id=\"4kY3L6\">human papillomavirus</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zO0rET&anker=Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-learningcard-id=\"zO0rET\" data-anker=\"Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-section-id=\"CPbqSF\" data-sememe-id=\"4kY3L6\">HPV</a>), particularly <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zO0rET&anker=Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-learningcard-id=\"zO0rET\" data-anker=\"Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-section-id=\"CPbqSF\" data-sememe-id=\"4kY3L6\">HPV</a> subtype 16, is responsible for a subset of oropharyngeal SCCs. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zO0rET&anker=Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-learningcard-id=\"zO0rET\" data-anker=\"Z579558c2c5c545a61649759bd9aa83fe\" data-section-id=\"CPbqSF\" data-sememe-id=\"4kY3L6\">HPV</a>-related <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z17c54b50884f6ae691e10c71ea7eccb6\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z17c54b50884f6ae691e10c71ea7eccb6\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\" data-sememe-id=\"prXLRz\">SCC</a> occurs predominantly in young men (age &lt;50 years; male-to-female <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=1j02zf&anker=Z72a88ef1b247b4893b9663b3737e8506\" data-learningcard-id=\"1j02zf\" data-anker=\"Z72a88ef1b247b4893b9663b3737e8506\" data-section-id=\"0GXeBz\" data-sememe-id=\"XAb9Rw\">ratio</a> of 4:1).<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point:</b></span> The most likely cause of an ulcerated tonsillar mass, especially with associated <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=do0oaS&anker=Zd683b39cdd22e209ef414f798da53d44\" data-learningcard-id=\"do0oaS\" data-anker=\"Zd683b39cdd22e209ef414f798da53d44\">cervical lymphadenopathy</a>, is oropharyngeal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z17c54b50884f6ae691e10c71ea7eccb6\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z17c54b50884f6ae691e10c71ea7eccb6\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\" data-sememe-id=\"prXLRz\">squamous-cell carcinoma</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wj0hcT&anker=Z0407a899d2d4b8de19aad106872a35e3\" data-learningcard-id=\"wj0hcT\" data-anker=\"Z0407a899d2d4b8de19aad106872a35e3\" data-section-id=\"DkY1J6\" data-sememe-id=\"NK1-g30\">Group A streptococcal pharyngitis</a> manifests acutely with bilateral tonsillar <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-section-id=\"0vXeA-\" data-sememe-id=\"3wYSir\">erythema</a> with <span data-sememe-id=\"gbaFGQ\">exudate</span>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Lf0w52&anker=Z396e86e88d3315f2dd9b99cf38d0942c\" data-learningcard-id=\"Lf0w52\" data-anker=\"Z396e86e88d3315f2dd9b99cf38d0942c\" data-sememe-id=\"Cj0qcT\">Infectious mononucleosis</a> is associated with acute symptoms of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">fever</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wj0hcT&anker=Za34e9f5b95a89605dd972411fe534aac\" data-learningcard-id=\"wj0hcT\" data-anker=\"Za34e9f5b95a89605dd972411fe534aac\" data-section-id=\"_kY5q6\">sore throat</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=iL0Jxg&anker=Z9a24d08ab67dee43098222189f24cc1a\" data-learningcard-id=\"iL0Jxg\" data-anker=\"Z9a24d08ab67dee43098222189f24cc1a\" data-sememe-id=\"OCYIHr\">lymphadenopathy</a>. Tonsillar findings include bilaterally enlarged, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-section-id=\"0vXeA-\" data-sememe-id=\"3wYSir\">erythematous</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=960NMS&anker=Za1bfe57362661c687aedbf6e279b7905\" data-learningcard-id=\"960NMS\" data-anker=\"Za1bfe57362661c687aedbf6e279b7905\" data-section-id=\"ZEcZ8V0\">tonsils</a> with <span data-sememe-id=\"gbaFGQ\">exudate</span>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=NT0-I2&anker=Z46cc87b0bb6d0dccc4fedce8fd20de06\" data-learningcard-id=\"NT0-I2\" data-anker=\"Z46cc87b0bb6d0dccc4fedce8fd20de06\" data-sememe-id=\"mP0V2T\">Non-Hodgkin lymphoma</a> occurs in the cervical region and Waldeyer ring, but it produces lesions that are fleshy, <span data-sememe-id=\"idVJpt0\">friable</span>, and nonulcerating.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>Tonsilloliths are calcified accumulations of bacteria, shedded <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Io0YWS&anker=Z23c08800c35f1f71236b85bd916db48b\" data-learningcard-id=\"Io0YWS\" data-anker=\"Z23c08800c35f1f71236b85bd916db48b\" data-section-id=\"4oc3XW0\" data-sememe-id=\"KubUHv\">epithelium</a>, and other debris that form in tonsillar crypts. Symptoms may include <span data-sememe-id=\"Y30nSf\">bad breath</span>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dp0ooS&anker=Z8dd8e7823b54e8fa23ebef7581c7073d\" data-learningcard-id=\"dp0ooS\" data-anker=\"Z8dd8e7823b54e8fa23ebef7581c7073d\">ear</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wj0hcT&anker=Za34e9f5b95a89605dd972411fe534aac\" data-learningcard-id=\"wj0hcT\" data-anker=\"Za34e9f5b95a89605dd972411fe534aac\" data-section-id=\"_kY5q6\">sore throat</a>, and tonsillar swelling. White debris can be cleaned from the tonsillar crypts. Findings can be unilateral, but <span data-sememe-id=\"SAcyQU0\">ulceration</span> of the tonsil does not occur. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">Pain</a> and cervical <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=iL0Jxg&anker=Z9a24d08ab67dee43098222189f24cc1a\" data-learningcard-id=\"iL0Jxg\" data-anker=\"Z9a24d08ab67dee43098222189f24cc1a\" data-sememe-id=\"OCYIHr\">adenopathy</a> are not caused by tonsilloliths.</div>",
