    {
      "text": "A 62-year-old man presents to the emergency department with throat discomfort and increasing difficulty swallowing solids. He has a 35 pack-year smoking history and drinks 3–4 beers daily. Physical examination shows asymmetrical tonsillar enlargement with firmness on palpation and a 2-cm mobile cervical lymph node. Vital signs are normal. What is the most appropriate next step in management?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Order CT scan of the neck with contrast"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Prescribe amoxicillin-clavulanate for 10 days"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Obtain throat culture and rapid strep test"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Refer to otolaryngology for endoscopy and biopsy"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Start prednisone and schedule follow-up in 1 week"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 4,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>While CT may be part of the workup, it is typically coordinated by ENT after other studies have been performed. An alternative step in management is required first in this patient.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>The combination of asymmetric tonsillar enlargement, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=do0oaS&anker=Zd683b39cdd22e209ef414f798da53d44\" data-learningcard-id=\"do0oaS\" data-anker=\"Zd683b39cdd22e209ef414f798da53d44\">cervical lymphadenopathy</a>, and significant <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ps0LDh&anker=Zbc0d0ff153bc5c7a27589815d0c842fd\" data-learningcard-id=\"ps0LDh\" data-anker=\"Zbc0d0ff153bc5c7a27589815d0c842fd\" data-section-id=\"FfWgLk0\" data-sememe-id=\"b31HSg0\">risk factors</a> suggests <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z8c3bce39ca977e0f872b6d9fb3be8cfb\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z8c3bce39ca977e0f872b6d9fb3be8cfb\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\" data-sememe-id=\"OHXIqz\">malignancy</a> rather than bacterial infection, making <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">antibiotic therapy</a> inappropriate for this patient.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>Rapid strep testing and throat culture are indicated for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wj0hcT&anker=Z19d5ecc633125a9c419ab01330d30ab3\" data-learningcard-id=\"wj0hcT\" data-anker=\"Z19d5ecc633125a9c419ab01330d30ab3\" data-section-id=\"8kYOp6\" data-sememe-id=\"ETb8sG\">acute pharyngitis</a>. However, this patient has chronic symptoms and concerning physical findings and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ps0LDh&anker=Zbc0d0ff153bc5c7a27589815d0c842fd\" data-learningcard-id=\"ps0LDh\" data-anker=\"Zbc0d0ff153bc5c7a27589815d0c842fd\" data-section-id=\"FfWgLk0\" data-sememe-id=\"b31HSg0\">risk factors</a> that suggest <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z8c3bce39ca977e0f872b6d9fb3be8cfb\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z8c3bce39ca977e0f872b6d9fb3be8cfb\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\" data-sememe-id=\"OHXIqz\">malignancy</a> rather than a viral infection.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) CORRECT:</h4>Correct -- The combination of persistent throat symptoms, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=D501mg&anker=Zd2d195657240f493374e95e2b75cc8cf\" data-learningcard-id=\"D501mg\" data-anker=\"Zd2d195657240f493374e95e2b75cc8cf\" data-section-id=\"-ZXDV9\" data-sememe-id=\"IQ0Yxf\">dysphagia</a>, asymmetrical tonsillar enlargement with firmness, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=do0oaS&anker=Zd683b39cdd22e209ef414f798da53d44\" data-learningcard-id=\"do0oaS\" data-anker=\"Zd683b39cdd22e209ef414f798da53d44\">cervical lymphadenopathy</a>, and significant smoking and <span data-sememe-id=\"NoW-Xm0\">alcohol</span> history requires prompt ENT referral for direct visualization and tissue <span data-sememe-id=\"sebtZG\">biopsy</span> to evaluate for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Cj0qcT&anker=Z1342771f3b15008407de6f01892bb4a2\" data-learningcard-id=\"Cj0qcT\" data-anker=\"Z1342771f3b15008407de6f01892bb4a2\" data-sememe-id=\"8DYOTr\">pharyngeal cancer</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=km0mfg&anker=Z3733d22ef7bb87f743207060acda0451\" data-learningcard-id=\"km0mfg\" data-anker=\"Z3733d22ef7bb87f743207060acda0451\" data-section-id=\"Pq1WA30\" data-sememe-id=\"8AbOlw\">Corticosteroids</a> are contraindicated in patients with suspected <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z8c3bce39ca977e0f872b6d9fb3be8cfb\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z8c3bce39ca977e0f872b6d9fb3be8cfb\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\" data-sememe-id=\"OHXIqz\">malignancy</a>. This patient's chronic symptoms and concerning physical findings require an alternative step in management.</div>",
